  "product": "atlas",
  "title": "Count MongoDB Search Results",
  "description": "The MongoDB Search count option adds a field to the metadata results document that displays a count of the search\nresults for the query. You can use count to determine the size of\nthe result set. You can use it in the $search\nor $searchMeta stage. You must use it in conjunction with\nthe MongoDB Search operators or collectors to display either the total number of documents or a\nlower bound on the number of documents that match the query.",
